        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1078381509" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4160635851148199518">I can&apos;t remember the last time I watched a football game. I think it was when I was in elementary school.<br/><br/>Even though I can&apos;t claim a team or quote stats, I was fascinated by this book. <br/><br/>The biggest takeaway was this: Professional football players are just people.. They&apos;re great athletes, but have insecure jobs and tons of stress. Fatsis&apos;s title, &quot;A Few Seconds of Panic,&quot; can be applied to the entire cadre of pro ballers, as long as it&apos;s changed to &quot;A Lifetime of Panic.&quot; <br/><br/>Fatsis is a great writer, </span>
  <span id="freeText4160635851148199518" style="display:none">I can't remember the last time I watched a football game. I think it was when I was in elementary school.<br /><br />Even though I can't claim a team or quote stats, I was fascinated by this book. <br /><br />The biggest takeaway was this: Professional football players are just people.. They're great athletes, but have insecure jobs and tons of stress. Fatsis's title, "A Few Seconds of Panic," can be applied to the entire cadre of pro ballers, as long as it's changed to "A Lifetime of Panic." <br /><br />Fatsis is a great writer, an even better reporter, and a really innovative researcher. His book is a insider's scoop to the NFL. Few others have been or will be able to create anything similar. </span>
  <a data-text-id="4160635851148199518" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

