<div id="review_3117868949" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3117868949" />
    <a title="John Vanderslice" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/12997929-john-vanderslice"><img alt="John Vanderslice" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442896368p2/12997929.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3117868949?book_show_action=true">Jan 02, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="John Vanderslice" class="user" itemprop="url" name="John Vanderslice" href="/user/show/12997929-john-vanderslice">John Vanderslice</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3117868949" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10562217906069677632">This is a fun book, and an engaging inside look at an NFL locker room. I have to admire Fatsis&apos;s guts in taking on this project, and the way he did it. And as he surely hoped when the project began, he did manage to find out a good deal about individual players as well as the whole NFL culture. A bit surprisingly, but nicely, he was eventually accepted by the &quot;real players,&quot;not quite as one of their own but certainly if nothing else as a honorary member of the club. Just like his hero and predec</span>
  <span id="freeText10562217906069677632" style="display:none">This is a fun book, and an engaging inside look at an NFL locker room. I have to admire Fatsis's guts in taking on this project, and the way he did it. And as he surely hoped when the project began, he did manage to find out a good deal about individual players as well as the whole NFL culture. A bit surprisingly, but nicely, he was eventually accepted by the "real players,"not quite as one of their own but certainly if nothing else as a honorary member of the club. Just like his hero and predecessor George Plimpton discovered when he carried out the participatory experiment for his famous Paper Lion book, Fatsis learns that the players are not at all the one-dimensional simpletons or icons that fans or detractors might want them to be. I highly recommend.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10562217906069677632" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


